article.headline: Buffalo 81, Niagara 79
article.story: LEWISTON, N.Y. (AP) -- Turner Battle's basket with 0.3 seconds remaining lifted Buffalo to an 81-79 non-conference win over Niagara on Saturday night. Buffalo led by as many as 12 points in the second half before Niagara went on an 18-6 run to tie the game at 79 when Juan Mendez sank two free throws with 20 seconds remaining. Buffalo then moved the ball down the court, and after a time out with 3.2 seconds remaining, got the ball to Battle at the top of the key for the game-winner. Battle led the Bulls (4-3) with 21 points, eight assists and five steals. Mark Bortz added 19 points off the bench for Buffalo and Mario Jordan had 15 points. Yassin Idbihi led the Bulls with 11 rebounds. Niagara (4-1), which entered the game third in the nation in scoring with an average of 93.5 points per game, was held to its lowest production of the season. Mendez, who was 10-of-10 from the foul line, led the Purple Eagles with 27 points. James Reaves had 17 points and Tremmell Darden finished with 14 points and 10 rebounds.
